We'll be talking with Louis Rossmann about his new venture the FULU Foundation and his work of Right to Repair. As the owner of a company focused on component level Apple repairs he has seen how devices have become more difficult to be able to be repaired over the years.

We'll talk about FULU, The Repair Preservation Group, his thoughts on the current state of repairability and right to repair and how a native New Yorker feels about Texas after a few years of living there.

https://www.linkedin.com/in/louis-rossmann-3a5396292/

https://www.linkedin.com/company/fulu-foundation-usa/

"FULU Foundation exists to restore and protect genuine ownership rights in the digital age. We're building a future where users have control over their devices, software, and digital tools. We believe people should have the ability to program their computers and hardware as they please."
title: Louis Rossmann - President @ FULU Foundation, Right to Repair
